                            <comment id="14494470" author="beobal" created="Tue, 14 Apr 2015 17:45:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Trival patch to prevent &lt;tt&gt;DropRoleStatement&lt;/tt&gt; from caching anything about non-existent roles and added a dtest &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/riptano/cassandra-dtest/pull/233&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Related: after &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-8967&quot; title=&quot;Allow RolesCache to be invalidated&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-8967&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-8967&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is done, test code could programatically invalidate the cache between the &lt;tt&gt;DROP&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;CREATE&lt;/tt&gt; statements, but I think this is worth doing anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14525976" author="iamaleksey" created="Sun, 3 May 2015 19:30:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk as &lt;tt&gt;6af82eddff9d2923ff5447120dac432bd0dadae4&lt;/tt&gt; (w/out a CHANGES.txt entry). Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
